SENEGAL star Sadio Mane will have a stadium named after him following his side’s victory in the Africa Cup of Nations in Cameroon. Senegal defeated Egypt in the final in Yaounde on 7 February, with Mane scoring the winner in a penalty shootout. At the Afcon Mane scored three goals and provided two assists as he was named Most Valuable Player of the tournament. Une semaine s’est passée depuis que le Sénégal est entré dans l’histoire à bras ouverts! ????#TotalEnergiesAFCON2021 | @CAF_Online | @caf_online_FR pic.twitter.com/ldVYExHGUG  Adboulaye Diop, mayor of Sedhiou, a town in Senegal, on Tuesday said the region’s football stadium will be named after Mane. "Sadio Mane has honoured all of Senegal, the Sedhiou region and the entire Casamance area," Abdoulaye Diop said as per liverpoolecho.co.uk "I have decided to name the Sedhiou stadium after him. "In doing so I wish to convey the gratitude of all the sons and daughters of the region towards him. "He has made all of mankind aware of Bambali and Sedhiou, the region's main town. "This is a gift that Sadio Mane truly deserves." In June last year, Mane has made a donation of 694 000 US dollars (R10 391 504,90) to help build a hospital in Bambali, back home in Senegal. Sadio Mane will have a stadium named in his honour in his home region of Sedhiou, following Senegal's AFCON win ????His legacy is secured ?? pic.twitter.com/znjXFJLrYl    